hepsplit is a program to split a big stdhep file to 
small files with small number of events. This tool 
is useful to run jobs at many grid nodes, avoiding
file transfers of a big file to many nodes.

To build, set STDHEPDIR to your stdhep directory 
then do make.

To run program, 
$ ./hepsplit

Command options are displayed by 
$ ./hepsplit --help

 
